               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Dǝggʷā, Antiphonary (fols. 2ra-74vc)
 I-1) Dǝggʷā, Antiphonary
                     (for the period of St John the Baptist, 1st Maskaram to 30th Ḫǝdār) (fols.
                     2ra-42va) 
 - Table of halleluiatic chants (fols. 41rb-42va)
 I-2)
                     Dǝggʷā, Antiphonary (for the period of Easter and the season of the Rains)
                     (fols. 43ra-74vc)
 II) Mǝʿrāf, The Common of the Office (fols.
                     76ra-100ra)
 II-1) Sacerdotal prayers and supplications (fol. 76ra-c
                     l.23)
 II-2) Wāzemā, The Office of Vigils (fols. 76rc l.24-78ra l.33)
                     II-3) Sǝbḥāta nagh, The Office of Matins (fols. 78ra l.34-81rc l.24)
 II-4)
                     Mawaddǝs, The Sunday Office (fols. 81rc l.25-91vb l.3)
 II-5) Sǝbḥāta nagh,
                     The Office of Matins (fols. 91vb l.3-93rc l.6)
 II-6) ʾAnqaṣa bǝrhān “Gate
                     of Light” (fols. 93rc l.6-95rb l.18)
 II-7) Kǝśtat za-ʾaryām, The festive
                     Office (fols. 95rb l.19-100ra)
 III) Mawāśǝʾt, Antiphonary for feasts and
                     funeral service (fols. 100rb-106vc)
 
 Additio 1.</summary>
